One says that M divides N, or that N is a multiple of M, if 
  
    
      
        
          a
          
            i
          
        
        ≤
        
          b
          
            i
          
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle a_{i}\leq b_{i}}
   for every i; that is, if A is componentwise not greater than B. In this case, the quotient 
  
    
      
        
          
