            (
            
              a
              
                n
              
            
            ,
            
              b
              
                n
              
            
            )
          
        
      
    
    {\textstyle x_{1}^{\min(a_{1},b_{1})}\cdots x_{n}^{\min(a_{n},b_{n})}}
   whose exponent vector is the componentwise minimum of A and B. The least common multiple lcm(M, N) is defined similarly with max instead of min.
One has

  
    
      
        lcm
        ⁡
        (
        M
        ,
        N
        )
        =
        
          
            
              M
              N
            
            
              gcd
              (
              M
              ,
              N
              )
            
          
        
